celebratory event\", \"from\": 433, \"to\": 454}, {\"ngram\": \"midday\", \"from\": 501, \"to\": 507}, {\"ngram\": \"the afternoon\", \"from\": 524, \"to\": 537}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A total of 64 women and 69 men competed for Team Ireland across 14 sports, winning seven medals in total.\", \"from\": 540, \"to\": 645, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 584, \"end\": 596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.976144531484627e-28, \"text\": \"Team Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A total\", \"from\": 540, \"to\": 547}, {\"ngram\": \"64 women\", \"from\": 551, \"to\": 559}, {\"ngram\": \"69 men\", \"from\": 564, \"to\": 570}, {\"ngram\": \"14 sports\", \"from\": 604, \"to\": 613}, {\"ngram\": \"seven medals\", \"from\": 623, \"to\": 635}, {\"ngram\": \"total\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 644}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Four gold medals were won across various events at the Paris games.\", \"from\": 647, \"to\": 714, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 702, \"end\": 707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.492593931009569e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Four gold medals\", \"from\": 647, \"to\": 663}, {\"ngram\": \"various events\", \"from\": 680, \"to\": 694}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Daniel Wiffen, 23, won gold in the men's 800m final and also took a bronze in the men's 1,500 metres final.\", \"from\": 716, \"to\": 823, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Daniel Wiffen\", \"from\": 716, \"to\": 729}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 743}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's 800m\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 761}, {\"ngram\": \"a bronze\", \"from\": 782, \"to\": 790}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's 1,500 metres\", \"from\": 794, \"to\": 816}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rhys McClenaghan, 25, won gold in the pommel horse final, in what he called his \\\"redemption story\\\".\", \"from\": 825, \"to\": 924, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 825, \"end\": 841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhys_McClenaghan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rhys McClenaghan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhys_McClenaghan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhys_McClenaghan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 851, \"to\": 855}, {\"ngram\": \"his \\\"redemption story\", \"from\": 901, \"to\": 922}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Three athletes retained their Olympic titles from the Tokyo games: Skibbereen rowers Paul O'Donovan and Fintan McCarthy in the men's lightweight double sculls; and Dubliner Kellie Harrington in the women's 60kg boxing event.\", \"from\": 926, \"to\": 1150, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 980, \"end\": 985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9887266104203964, \"rank\": 0.011401927953064769, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1011, \"end\": 1025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_O'Donovan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paul O'Donovan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_O'Donovan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_O'Donovan\"}, {\"begin\": 1030, \"end\": 1045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fintan_McCarthy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fintan McCarthy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fintan_McCarthy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fintan_McCarthy\"}, {\"begin\": 1099, \"end\": 1116