e medal\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1200}, {\"ngram\": \"the 100 metre breaststroke\", \"from\": 1204, \"to\": 1230}, {\"ngram\": \"Daire Lynch\", \"from\": 1262, \"to\": 1273}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1289}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking at the event, the Taoiseach said the team had done the country proud, with the public glued to their screens for the last two weeks.\", \"from\": 1292, \"to\": 1433, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1319, \"end\": 1328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taoiseach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.398625254552982e-35, \"text\": \"Taoiseach\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taoiseach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taoiseach\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 1304, \"to\": 1313}, {\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 1334, \"to\": 1342}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 1352, \"to\": 1363}, {\"ngram\": \"the public\", \"from\": 1376, \"to\": 1386}, {\"ngram\": \"their screens\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1409}, {\"ngram\": \"the last two weeks\", \"from\": 1414, \"to\": 1432}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They have done us so proud.\", \"from\": 1437, \"to\": 1465, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1453, \"to\": 1455}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I was just saying backstage that there has been very little work done in this country for the last fortnight because everyone opportunity we have had we have all been glued to our screens.\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1654, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"very little work\", \"from\": 1514, \"to\": 1530}, {\"ngram\": \"this country\", \"from\": 1539, \"to\": 1551}, {\"ngram\": \"the last fortnight\", \"from\": 1556, \"to\": 1574}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone opportunity\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1603}, {\"ngram\": \"our screens\", \"from\": 1642, \"to\": 1653}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"On your behalf I just want to say a massive thank you to these men and women who have inspired our nation.\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1763, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your behalf\", \"from\": 1660, \"to\": 1671}, {\"ngram\": \"a massive thank\", \"from\": 1691, \"to\": 1706}, {\"ngram\": \"these men\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1723}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 1728, \"to\": 1733}, {\"ngram\": \"our nation\", \"from\": 1752, \"to\": 1762}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Go raibh m\\u00edle maith agat.\", \"from\": 1764, \"to\": 1789, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"agat\", \"from\": 1784, \"to\": 1788}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have talked a lot about lighting flames, and what these men and women have done is lit a flame in so many little tiny kids ... who now believe they too can be the very best in the world, they can represent Ireland, they can win medals.\", \"from\": 1791, \"to\": 2030, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2001, \"end\": 2008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999996344682345, \"rank\": 3.655320008919353e-07, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 1812}, {\"ngram\": \"lighting flames\", \"from\": 1819, \"to\": 1834}, {\"ngram\": \"these men\", \"from\": 1845, \"to\": 1854}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 1859, \"to\": 1864}, {\"ngram\": \"a flame\", \"from\": 1882, \"to\": 1889}, {\"ngram\": \"so many little tiny kids\", \"from\": 1893, \"to\": 1917}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1971, \"to\": 1980}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 2023, \"to\": 2029}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's what they have done, and what we will do now is invest in sport because we believe in these athletes and that's going to be the legacy of these Paris games.\\\"\", \"from\": 2032, \"to\": 2197, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2184, \"end\": 2189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.492593931009569e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 2098, \"to\": 2103}, {\"ngram\": \"these athletes\", \"from\": 2126, \"to\": 2140}, {\"ngram\": \"the legacy\", \"from\": 2164, \"to\": 2174}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympians arrive at Dublin Airport ahead of homecoming Swimmer Daniel Wiffen said he felt all of Ireland supporting him as he won Olympic gold and bronze medals.\", \"from\": 2199, \"to\": 2363, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2299, \"end\": 2306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999996344682345, \"rank\": 3.655320008919353e-07, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympians\", \"from\": 2199, \"to\": 2208}, {\"ngram\": \"Dublin Airport\", \"from\": 2219, \"to\": 2233}, {\"ngram\": \"Swimmer Daniel Wiffen\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2275}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic gold and bronze medals\", \"from\": 2329, \"to\": 2359}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I definitely felt a whole country backing me going into it.\", \"from\": 2365, \"to\": 2425, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a whole country\", \"from\": 2384, \"to\": 2399}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Walking out into the stadium was crazy, you always feel those nerves but you got to level your head and get in and know everyone back home is supporting you and they want the gold medal as much as you do,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2426, \"to\": 2640, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the stadium\", \"from\": 2443, \"to\": 2454}, {\"ngram\": \"those nerves\", \"from\": 2482, \"to\": 2494}, {\"ngram\": \"your head\", \"from\": 2516, \"to\": 2525}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 2546, \"to\": 2554}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold medal\", \"from\": 2597, \"to\": 2611}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Going into the 800m freestyle final the Armagh swimmer said he \\\"definitely knew\\\" he was going to win gold, particularly in the last 50m of the race.\", \"from\": 2642, \"to\": 2790, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2682, \"end\": 2688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armagh_GAA\", \"score\": 0.9999987799158756, \"rank\": 1.1813746053958125e-06, \"text\": \"Armagh\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armagh_GAA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armagh_GAA\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 2743, \"to\": 2747}, {\"ngram\": \"the last 50m\", \"from\": 2765, \"to\": 2777}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 2781, \"to\": 2789}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I backed myself day and night and that's exactly what I did.\", \"from\": 2792, \"to\": 2853, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"exactly what\", \"from\": 2834, \"to\": 2846}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wiffen missed out on being a flag bearer at the closing ceremony in Paris but said he is feeling much better now after a trip to hospital last night.\", \"from\": 2855, \"to\": 3004, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2923, \"end\": 2928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.492593931009569e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wiffen\", \"from\": 2855, \"to\": 2861}, {\"ngram\": \"a flag bearer\", \"from\": 2882, \"to\": 2895}, {\"ngram\": \"the closing ceremony\", \"from\": 2899, \"to\": 2919}, {\"ngram\": \"a trip\", \"from\": 2974, \"to\": 2980}, {\"ngram\": \"hospital\", \"from\": 2984, \"to\": 2992}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Looking ahead to LA 2028, Wiffen said he expects his brother Nathan to be competing alongside him.\", \"from\": 3006, \"to\": 3104, \"entities